Dear FoLLI members,

By the present mail which is being sent to all current members of the
Association for Logic, Language and Information (FoLLI) we are calling
for nominations for the following positions in the FoLLI Management Board:

1) President
2) Vice-President
3) Secretary
4) Treasurer
5) Senior Member

A description of their tasks accordingly to FoLLI Bylaws
(available at www.folli.org) follows at the end of this mail.

Nomination will be open till Friday, 11th of May.  Self-nominations
are not possible.  All nominees should be contacted in advance to
submission of nominations and should have explicitly accepted to take
the position if elected.  Nominees will be listed in the FoLLI site.
After the final list of nominations has been compiled, a call for
elections will be issued.

All nominations should be sent to carlos.areces@gmail.com

On behalf of the FoLLI Management Board, 
Carlos Areces

====================================================================
Description of the tasks for the different members of the Board:

President.  The President shall be the principal executive officer of
the Association and shall, in general, supervise and control the
business and affairs of the Association.  He or she shall preside at
all the General Meeting sand the meetings of the Management Board.

Vice President. In the absence of the President or in the event of his
or her inability or refusal to act, the vice President shall perform
the duties of the President, and when so acting, shall have all the
powers of and be subject to all the restrictions upon the President.

Secretary.  The Secretary shall keep, or cause to be kept, the minutes
of the General Meetings, and meetings of the Management Board; see
that all notices are duly given in accordance with the provisions of
the By-Laws or as required by law; be custodian of the records;
collect nominations for elections, and, in general, perform all duties
incident to the office of Secretary and such other duties as, from
time to time, may be assigned to him or her by the President or by the
Management Board.

Treasurer.  The Treasurer shall have charge and custody of and be
responsible for all funds and securities of the Association; receive
and give receipts for monies due and payable to the Association from
any source whatsoever, and deposit all such monies in the name of the
Association in such banks, trust companies, or other depositaries as
shall be selected by the Management Board.  The Treasurer shall
perform all duties incident to the office of Treasurer, in particular
the preparation of the annual budget and financial statement to be
presented to the annual Management Board and General Meeting. 

Senior Member. The outgoing President is by default nominated for
election as Senior Member.  He or she shall have act as adviser to the 
Management Board. 
